Help Type: command
Command: spinedigest queue add

Purpose:
  Create one graph or summary job for one `.sdpub` chapter.

Usage:
  spinedigest queue add <archive.sdpub> --chapter <id> [--to graph|summary] --accept-cost [--boost] [--llm <json>] [--prompt <text>]

Cost and time:
  - Graph and summary jobs call an LLM, consume tokens, may incur provider charges, and can run for minutes to hours on large chapters.
  - `--accept-cost` is required when a job is actually added.
  - Run `spinedigest estimate <archive.sdpub> --stage summary` before queueing large batches.

Options:
  --chapter <id>       Required chapter id.
  --to graph|summary   Target stage. Default: summary.
  --accept-cost        Explicitly acknowledge LLM cost and wait time.
  --boost              Insert the new job at the front of the queued jobs.
  --llm <json>         Override LLM configuration for this job.
  --prompt <text>      Override extraction prompt for this job.

Scheduling:
  - New jobs are appended by default.
  - `--boost` moves the new job ahead of other queued work, but it does not preempt running jobs.
  - One active job may exist for one `(archive, chapter)` pair.

Examples:
  spinedigest queue add book.sdpub --chapter 3 --to graph --accept-cost
  spinedigest queue add book.sdpub --chapter 3 --to summary --accept-cost --boost

Next:
  spinedigest queue list --input book.sdpub
  spinedigest queue watch <job-id> --jsonl
